The paper discusses the application of MIMO in wireless systems, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). It also discusses the different models and methods of combining signals, which can be categorized under systems and control (cs.SY) and multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also touches on the use of MIMO in spatial diversity and spatial multiplexing, which can be classified under augmented reality (cs.AR).
